others  including people with changing abilities due to aging  Web accessibility encompasses all disabilities that affect access to the web  including visual  auditory  physical  speech  cognitive  and neurological disabilities About this site  the Illinois Board of Higher Education  IBHE  the Illinois Information Technology Accessibility Act  IITAA  and other federal and state legislative acts applying to electronic resources Illinois Board of Higher Education  IBHE Illinois Information Technology Accessibility Act  IITAA Why websites must be accessiblie and how to join the committee  n n nUser icon n n n n n n nWhy Websites Must Be Accessible n User icon  n n nSpeech bubble icon n n n n n n nJoin the Committee n Speech bubble icon UIC Digital Accessibility Committee Mission  This committee supports the campus in the process of advancing Web accessibility through  The Digital Accessibility Committee is dedicated to the long term effort of improving the accessibility of our campus websites  but will need the active cooperation and efforts of campus webmasters for accessibility to be implemented at UIC Resource and Site Checks The Digital Accessibility Committee is available to support campus webmasters  For more information and help with checking a site for accessibility  contact the committee contact the committee Digital Accessibility News and Events  Reopening Door for Web Accessibility Complaints  Reopening Door for Web Accessibility Complaints    Colleges Hit With ADA Lawsuits    Colleges Hit With ADA Lawsuits    Accessibility      days of digital accessibility gifts during the season of giving and sharing    Accessibility      days of digital accessibility gifts during the season of giving and sharing  n nUIC Logo n n n n UIC Logo  n          Digital Accessibility Committee n         Contact               dag listserv uic edu Social Media Accounts UIC edu links UIC edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus Directory Disability Resources Emergency Information Even